main event: On May 7, 1956, in Rochester, Indiana, a stationary round object, three inches in diameter with silver and green color, was observed. It was identified as a fixed beacon light by a scrambled aircraft.
interesting points: Observation was made by a civilian-military source.
The UFO was described as a small round object with specific colors.
One aircraft was scrambled to identify the UFO as a fixed beacon light.
The report indicates the possibility of the object being astronomical in nature.
There were no photographs included with the report.
sighted object: stationary round object, three inches in diameter, with silver and green color
